Iggy Azalea has unleashed a fresh track and addressed her musical hiatus via Twitter, ahead of the release of her all-new album later this month.The Australian rapper premiered her new single &#8220;Can&#8217;t Lose&#8221;, featuring rapper Lil Uzi Vert, via Spotify today, following a candid series of Tweets to fans on Thursday where she apologised for the wait on new music.During the social media reveal, Azalea wrote: &#8220;I hope my fans understand my life has been filled with so many personal changes. I felt it was important I made some creative changes too &#8211; I needed my album to reflect where my head&#8217;s at in 2017.&#8221;Her upcoming sophomore major label album, &#8220;Digital Distortion&#8221; &#8211; which reportedly features collaborations with Bebe Rexha, Jess Glynne, and production trio The Invisible Men &#8211; is set to be released throughout the month of March (via EW).Azalea also revealed that she had also decided to include &#8220;Can&#8217;t Lose&#8221; from her upcoming album on the new Def Jam #DirectDeposit tape, which is available now on iTunes.-Relaxnews